What is a Repository?

Think of it as a bridge between your Java application and the database.

Application
      │
      ▼
EmployeeRepository
      │
      ▼
Hibernate
      │
      ▼
Database

Instead of writing SQL yourself, you simply call methods on the repository.



####  The Magic of Spring Data JPA

When Spring Boot starts, it sees:

extends JpaRepository

Spring says:

"I'll generate the implementation automatically."

Internally, something like this happens:

You Write

EmployeeRepository

↓

Spring Boot Generates

EmployeeRepositoryImpl

↓

Contains save()

Contains delete()

Contains findAll()

Contains findById()

Contains count()

Contains existsById()

You never see this generated class, but Spring creates it at runtime.